{quote}

Often when Bamboo is integrated with LDAP, the Bamboo instance may have more than 100 (LDAP) groups.

In such cases, "fhe groups are listed 10 at a time with links to page through all the groups up to 100 groups (page 10). If you have more, you don't get a link to go to page 11"
- From [BSP-288|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/BSP-288]
{quote}
I have discovered that there is a problem when trying to browse through more than 100 groups in Bamboo. When you go to the Manage Groups page, the groups are listed 10 at a time with links to page through all the groups up to 100 groups (page 10). If you have more, you don't get a link to go to page 11. The workaround I've discovered for this is to hack the URL and set the startIndex to "100" and it seems to reset the paging and let you see the next set of pages.
{quote}

